# DOM – Relation

## Concepts

- self: current node
- parent: direct parent node
- children: direct child nodes
- ancestor: parent, grandparent, etc.
- descendant: children, grandchildren, etc.
- sibling: same level, same parent
- following: nodes on the right side (excluding children)
- preceding: nodes on the left side (excluding ancestors)
- following-sibling: next siblings
- preceding-sibling: previous siblings

---

# XPath – Advanced Methods


## Wildcard

```xpath
//div
//*
```

- `*` matches all elements

---

## child

```xpath
//form[@id='test-form']/child::button
```

- Select direct children

---

## descendant

```xpath
//form[@id='test-form']/descendant::input
```

- Select all descendants

---

## parent

```xpath
//button[text()='Create Test Case']/parent::form
```

- Select parent node

---

## ancestor

```xpath
//button[@class='btn-edit']/ancestor::table
```

- Select ancestor nodes

---

## following-sibling

```xpath
//label[@for='testName']/following-sibling::input
```

- Select next sibling

---

## preceding-sibling

```xpath
//button[@class='btn-reset']/preceding-sibling::button
```

- Select previous sibling

---

## following

```xpath
//h2[text()='Test Cases List']/following::button[@class='btn-run']
```

- Select all nodes after current node

---

## preceding

```xpath
//h2[text()='Test Execution Results']/preceding::td[@class='priority-high']
```

- Select all nodes before current node

---

## ancestor-or-self

```xpath
//table[@id='test-table']/ancestor-or-self::span
```

---

## descendant-or-self

```xpath
//table[@id='test-table']/descendant-or-self::span
```

---

# XPath Axes Summary

```xpath
//tag/relationship::tagname[@attr='value']
```

Relationships:

- parent
- child
- ancestor
- descendant
- following
- preceding
- following-sibling
- preceding-sibling

---

# XPath Advanced Syntax

## Attribute

```xpath
//tag[@attribute='value']
```

---

## AND / OR

```xpath
//element[@a='1' and @b='2']
//element[@a='1' or @b='2']
```

---

## text()

```xpath
//element[text()='exact text']
```

---

## normalize-space()

```xpath
normalize-space()
```

- Remove extra spaces

---

## contains()

```xpath
//element[contains(text(), 'text')]
//element[contains(@attr, 'value')]
```

